case.name: Dong v Minister for Immigration & Citizenship (No. 2) [2009] FCA 752 (10 June 2009)

citation.tocase: Schwart v Minister for Immigration and Multicultural and Indigenous Affairs [2003] FCA 169
citation.text: The Minister does not dispute the proposition of law asserted in the applicant's affidavit (see Schwart v Minister for Immigration and Multicultural and Indigenous Affairs [2003] FCA 169 at [16] and Minister for Immigration and Multicultural and Indigenous Affairs v Schwart [2003] FCAFC 229). However, the Minister disputes the factual assertion that the Tribunal failed to describe the applicant's visa correctly.
